iNat Data Analysis

Joey Hulbert

4/9/2022

Purpose

The purpose of this markdown document is to list the steps completed for analysis of the iNaturalist data. Below we conduct a random forest analysis using only the explanitory variables in the iNaturalist dataset.

Data

The data used in the below models are described in the Data Wrangle folder.

## # A tibble: 2  2
## # Groups:   field.tree.canopy.symptoms [2]
##   field.tree.canopy.symptoms     n
##   <fct>                      <int>
## 1 Healthy                      813
## 2 Unhealthy                    695
  • Note the following fields were removed because theyre not explanatory variables for the below model
    • field.optionalwere.there.any.other.unhealthy.plant.species.on.the.site.
    • field.optionaltiming.of.symptoms.estimate
    • field.optionalestimated.time.spent.to.make.this.observation.of.minutes.
    • field.optionalcan.we.follow.up.with.you.
    • field.percent.canopy.affected.
    • field.number.of.additional.unhealthy.trees..of.same.species..in.area..within.sight.
    • field.percent.of.trees..of.same.species..within.sight.that.are.unhealthy
    • field.notes
